w installed and ready for use.

This API is released in Open Beta

Command line applications (use in a Terminal Window)

SoapySDRUtil --info
will show the drivers installed

SoapySDRUtil --find="driver=sdrplay"
will display found RSP devices

SoapySDRUtil --probe="driver=sdrplay"
will display detailed information on the found RSP devices

You shouldn't need to, but if you do need to manually restart the API service, type the following into a Terminal Window...

sudo launchctl stop com.sdrplay.sdrplay_service

The SoapySDRPlay library is still in development and not something SDRplay has developed.

Any RSP/API related issues can be raised on our support system:
https://www.sdrplay.com/support

SDRplay
